<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1632,2017]" box="[199,681,1740,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1740,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Description.</emphasis>
BL: 3.00 mm, BW: 1.00 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1632,2017]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Male. Body dark brown to black, with antenna, mouthparts and legs yellowish to light brown, elytra golden yellow with median basal and subapical median brown spots. Body subcylindrical and covered with fine microsetae. Dorsum of head, pronotum and elytra with sculpturing.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1632,2017]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,392]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="148" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
Antenna with antennomeres 
<number box="[520,575,1884,1909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" value="8.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="6.0">6–11</number>
increasingly wide and forming somewhat a club. Clypeus with emargination on its anterior margin. Epistomal suture arcuate. Labrum transverse, with anterior margin slightly emarginate. Cuticular process of internal fringe of epipharyngeal lobes with serrated apex. Mandibles tridentate. Mentum subquadrate. Submentum extending slightly onto venter of head, posterior margin strongly V-shaped. Gular sutures fused anteriorly. Pronotum wider than long (PW/PL: 
<number box="[784,836,1888,1912]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" value="1.39">1.39</number>
), with anterior pronotal angles produced, posterior margin curved. Prototergosternal suture present, procoxal fissure closed, protrochantin concealed. Elytra slightly longer than wide (EL/BW: 
<number box="[470,522,1960,1984]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" value="1.14">1.14</number>
), with a sclerotized median tip on the posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1257,1959,1984]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="147">
Fig. 
<number box="[1241,1257,1960,1983]" pageId="2" pageNumber="147" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow), elytral epipleural ridge complete. Sternite VII without median lobe and truncate on posterior margin. Tergite VIII with folds on anterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[435,516,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[486,516,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow), with pores at the front of the antecosta (
<figureCitation box="[1057,1138,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[1109,1138,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
), and truncate on posterior margin. Posterior margin of sternite VIII truncate. Tergite IX with ventral struts on male. Tergite X truncate on posterior margin and with a membranous projection. Aedeagus follows pattern of 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1296,224,247]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1296,224,247]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">punctatissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group with parameres slender and cylindrical, and median lobe bulbous. Aedeagus with subapical emargination on median lobe in lateral view and apex curved (
<figureCitation box="[572,639,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[624,639,296,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow).
</paragraph>
