<collectingCountry box="[1359,1431,1654,1679]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="149" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1582,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1690,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Remarks.</emphasis>
The anneloid spermatheca of 
<emphasis box="[660,856,1691,1715]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicName box="[660,853,1691,1715]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">Bledius borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[865,956,1690,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[865,956,1690,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
places it within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1189,1355,1691,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimus">
<emphasis box="[1189,1355,1691,1714]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">punctatissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. 
<emphasis box="[151,347,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicName box="[151,343,1726,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">Bledius borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[355,445,1726,1751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[355,445,1726,1751]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[592,741,1726,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">
<emphasis box="[592,741,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. fernandezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[797,994,1727,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimus">
<emphasis box="[797,994,1727,1750]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. punctatissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, all having the procoxal fissure closed, with the protrochantin concealed. 
<emphasis box="[534,731,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicName box="[534,727,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">Bledius borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[739,829,1762,1787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[739,829,1762,1787]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be easily differentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[1209,1358,1763,1787]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">
<emphasis box="[1209,1358,1763,1787]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. fernandezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the posterior margin of the tergite VIII, this being truncate on 
<emphasis box="[830,969,1798,1822]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicName box="[830,965,1798,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">B. borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[979,1071,1798,1823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[979,1071,1798,1823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1089,1173,1798,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[1144,1173,1799,1823]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) and emarginate on 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. fernandezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[287,370,1834,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 15" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1190,1213]" captionTargetBox="[153,1426,194,1168]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1169]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 15. Bledius depressus, sp. nov.. 12, tergite X (detail of dorsal depression); 13, tergite X magnified (detail of the long membranous projection); 14, aedeagus, lateral view (detail of pair of sclerites); 15, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256528/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[342,370,1834,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[412,749,1834,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" refString="Caron, E. &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. (2007) Bledius Leach from southern Brazil (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 51 (4), 452 - 457. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262007000400008" type="journal article" year="2007">
Caron &amp; Ribeiro-Costa 
<number box="[688,749,1835,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Also, the spermatheca of 
<emphasis box="[1065,1197,1835,1859]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicName box="[1065,1193,1835,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">B borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1206,1299,1834,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1206,1299,1834,1859]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is long and slender (
<figureCitation box="[248,317,1870,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[301,317,1871,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="9.0">9</number>
</figureCitation>
), while the spermatheca of 
<taxonomicName box="[630,780,1870,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fernandezi">
<emphasis box="[630,780,1870,1894]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. fernandezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is short and with the base wider than the apex (
<figureCitation box="[1324,1405,1870,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1972,1995]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,1057,1945]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1057,1951]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Bledius externus. 16, tergite VII; 17, tergite VIII; 18, sternite VIII; 19 – 20, aedeagus, ventral and lateral view; 21, spermatheca. Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256529/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
Fig. 
<number box="[1377,1405,1870,1895]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Caron" box="[151,482,1906,1931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" refString="Caron, E. &amp; Ribeiro-Costa, C. S. (2007) Bledius Leach from southern Brazil (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 51 (4), 452 - 457. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0085 - 56262007000400008" type="journal article" year="2007">
Caron &amp; Ribeiro-Costa 
<number box="[421,482,1907,1931]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This species can be differentiated from 
<taxonomicName box="[948,1146,1907,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimus">
<emphasis box="[948,1146,1907,1930]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. punctatissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the anterior margin of the pronotum, this being with the anterior angles produced in 
<emphasis box="[848,985,1942,1966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicName box="[848,981,1942,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">B. borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[993,1083,1942,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[993,1083,1942,1967]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1139,1336,1943,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimus">
<emphasis box="[1139,1336,1943,1966]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. punctatissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the anterior margin broadly arcuate to truncate (Fig. 
<number box="[698,726,1978,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="75.0">75</number>
of 
<bibRefCitation author="Herman" box="[763,920,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" refString="Herman, L. H. (1972) Revision of Bledius and related genera. Part I. The aequatorialis, mandibularis, and semiferrugineus groups and two new genera (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 149 (2), 111 - 254." type="journal article" year="1972">
Herman 
<number box="[860,920,1979,2003]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1972.0">1972</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<bibRefCitation author="Herman" box="[199,370,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" refString="Herman, L. H. (1986) Revision of Bledius. Part IV. Classification of species groups, phylogeny, natural history, and catalogue (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Oxytelinae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 184, 1 - 368." type="journal article" year="1986">
Herman (
<number box="[303,361,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="1986.0">1986</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
states that species of 
<taxonomicName box="[610,694,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[610,694,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Bledius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a double reservoir on tergite IX, although, in 
<emphasis box="[1260,1396,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1392,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">B. borzonei</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, besides the normal IX reservoirs, the new species has folds and emarginations on the anterior margin of tergite VIII, showing pores at the front of its antecosta (
<figureCitation box="[797,893,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1490,1513]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,445,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,445,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 11. Bledius borzonei, sp. nov.. 7, elytra (detail of posterior pit); 8, aedeagus, lateral view; 9, spermatheca; 10, tergite VIII (detail of anterior folds); 11, tergite VIII magnified (detail of the anterior folds and pores). Scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256527/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Figs. 
<number box="[863,893,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
, arrow, and 
<number box="[1037,1066,224,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="11.0">11</number>
). These characteristics might be related to tergal glands, but no reservoir was found in this region. 
<bibRefCitation author="Steidle" box="[883,1178,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" refString="Steidle, J. L. &amp; Dettner, K. (1993) Chemistry and morphology of the tergal gland of freeliving adult Aleocharinae (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae) and its phylogenetic significance. Systematic Entomology, 18, 149 - 168. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1993. tb 00659. x" type="journal article" year="1993">
Steidle and Dettner (
<number box="[1112,1170,260,284]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
found similar pores on tergite VII for some species of 
<taxonomicName box="[499,652,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Aleocharinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName box="[199,388,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,388,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Bledius borzonei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[402,491,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[402,491,332,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was sampled in the edge of a tidal creek, located at mouth of Vaza-Barris river (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 32" captionStartId="9.[151,264,861,884]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,199,832]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,841]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 32. Map of the coastal region of Sergipe where the holotypes of Bledius borzonei, sp. nov. and B. depressus, sp. nov. were collected. (Google Earth)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256531/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,368,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="32.0">32</number>
</figureCitation>
). This place is an estuarine beach (i.e., a low-energy environment) characterized by soft sediments composed by very fine sand. The samples were taken with PVC cores (
<quantity box="[805,869,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" unit="cm" value="10.0">10cm</quantity>
of diameter) and randomly distributed around the driftline (
<figureCitation box="[258,343,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 33" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1949,1972]" captionTargetBox="[151,1430,1204,1924]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,964,1928]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 33. Habitat of the holotypes of B. borzonei, sp. nov. and B. depressus, sp. nov. showing the drift line (seta)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[312,343,440,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
). In this place, 
<taxonomicName box="[520,710,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[520,710,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Bledius borzonei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[725,816,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[725,816,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
was found coexisting with 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1274,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="depressus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1132,1274,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">B. depressus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1283,1374,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1283,1374,439,464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 34" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1178,1201]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,193,1153]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,193,1157]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 34. Detail (i. e., seta) showing the discretes horizontal tumuli of Bledius borzonei, sp. nov. and B. depressus, sp. nov.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/256533/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,476,500]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[202,391,476,500]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Bledius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="borzonei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[202,391,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">Bledius borzonei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[405,494,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[405,494,476,501]" pageId="4" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have not been found at local exposed ocean beaches yet.
</paragraph>
